summary: Completed comprehensive testing of automotive parts supplier portal. Backend APIs working well (16/18 tests passed), frontend login flows and dashboards functioning correctly for both admin and supplier roles.

critical_bugs.issue: Returns HTTP 520 server error when creating new parts

minor_issues.issue: Returns 403 instead of 401 for unauthorized access

passed_tests: Admin login with admin@rvparts.com works correctly
Supplier login with supplier1@metalworks.com works correctly
Admin dashboard displays with all tabs (Overview, Suppliers, All Parts, Audit Logs)
Supplier dashboard shows stats tiles (completed, incomplete, needs review)
Parts table displays with expandable child components
Role-based access control working (suppliers blocked from admin endpoints)
Parts stats endpoint (/api/parts/stats) working for both roles
Parts list endpoint (/api/parts) working for both roles
Suppliers endpoint (/api/suppliers) working for admin, blocked for supplier
Audit logs endpoint (/api/audit-logs) working for admin, blocked for supplier
Navigation between admin dashboard tabs working
Logout functionality working for both roles
action_item_for_main_agent: Fix part creation API endpoint - currently returning HTTP 520 server error when suppliers try to create new parts via POST /api/parts
